<header class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">Resources</div>
    <h1>Who to call.</h1>
    <p class="deck">
      Free legal help, tenant unions in every borough, the coalitions doing the political work,
      and the government offices that are supposed to be on your side. Nobody should have to
      hunt for this.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">

    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Start here</h2>
    <p class="lead">If you don't know where to begin, begin with one of these. They're free, and they'll point you the rest of the way.</p>

    <div class="quick">
      <div class="q">
        <h3>Met Council on Housing<br>Tenants' Rights Hotline</h3>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:2129790611">212-979-0611</a>
        <p>NYC's oldest tenant organization. Volunteer counselors — not lawyers, but among the most knowledgeable people on tenant rights in this city. Mon &amp; Wed 1:30–8pm, Tue 5:30–8pm, Fri 1:30–5pm.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="q">
        <h3>Right to Counsel<br>Eviction Free NYC</h3>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:7185571379">718-557-1379</a>
        <p>Free legal representation in Housing Court. Every ZIP code, regardless of immigration status. Also connects you to an organizing group near you — <a href="https://www.evictionfreenyc.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">evictionfreenyc.org</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="q">
        <h3>Legal Aid — Housing Justice Unit<br>Group Advocacy</h3>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:2125777988">212-577-7988</a>
        <p><strong>This line exists specifically to help you start a tenants association.</strong> If you're reading this page because your building is expiring, this is the call. Mon–Fri, 10am–4pm.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="q">
        <h3>NYC Tenant Helpline</h3>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:311">311</a>
        <p>Free over-the-phone legal advice through the city's Office of Civil Justice, Mon–Fri 9am–5pm. Or email <a href="mailto:civiljustice@hra.nyc.gov">civiljustice@hra.nyc.gov</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ LEGAL ============ -->
    <h2 style="margin-top:56px">Free legal help</h2>

    <div class="orgs">
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://takerootjustice.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TakeRoot Justice</a></h4>
          <p>Legal, participatory research and policy support for grassroots groups. They represent the tenants of 63 Tiffany Place, including me.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://legalaidnyc.org/get-help/housing-problems/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Legal Aid Society</a></h4>
          <p>Offices in every borough.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:right;font-size:14px;color:var(--slate);line-height:1.8">
          <a class="tel" href="tel:7187223100" style="font-size:14px">Brooklyn 718-722-3100</a><br>
          <a class="tel" href="tel:2124263000" style="font-size:14px">Manhattan 212-426-3000</a><br>
          <a class="tel" href="tel:7189914600" style="font-size:14px">Bronx 718-991-4600</a><br>
          <a class="tel" href="tel:7182862450" style="font-size:14px">Queens 718-286-2450</a><br>
          <a class="tel" href="tel:3474225333" style="font-size:14px">Staten Is. 347-422-5333</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.legalservicesnyc.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Legal Services NYC</a></h4>
          <p>Citywide network of neighborhood offices.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://mobilizationforjustice.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mobilization for Justice</a></h4>
          <p>Anti-eviction programs for low-income tenants, seniors, and SRO residents. Fact sheets in English, Spanish, and Chinese.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://housingcourtanswers.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Housing Court Answers</a></h4>
          <p>If you have a case in Housing Court. Tue–Thu, 9am–5pm.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:2129624795">212-962-4795</a>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://catholicmigration.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Catholic Migration Services</a></h4>
          <p>Housing, immigration, and workers' rights. Serves tenants regardless of faith or immigration status. Strong tenant organizing arm.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ UNIONS ============ -->
    <h2 style="margin-top:60px">Tenant unions &amp; organizing groups</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      A lawyer defends you in court. <strong>An organizer helps you win before you get there.</strong>
      You want both, and most tenants only ever find the first.
    </p>

    <!-- BROOKLYN -->
    <div class="boro">
      <div class="boro-head"><h3>Brooklyn</h3></div>
      <div class="orgs">
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://www.crownheightstenantunion.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Crown Heights Tenant Union</a></h4>
            <p>Founded 2013. One of the most effective tenant unions in the city — rent strikes, eviction defense, and direct action against predatory equity. They also help other neighborhoods start their own unions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://www.carrollgardensassociation.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Southwest Brooklyn Tenants Union</a> <span class="tagpill hot">Ours</span></h4>
            <p>Convened through the Carroll Gardens Association. This is the union we organized with at 63 Tiffany Place.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4>Flatbush Tenant Coalition <span class="tagpill">now Flatbush Power</span></h4>
            <p>A member-led coalition of tenant associations across Flatbush, East Flatbush, and South Crown Heights.</p>
          </div>
          <a class="tel" href="tel:7186352623">718-635-2623</a>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://www.tenantunionflatbush.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tenant Union Flatbush</a></h4>
            <p>Tenant-led, fighting high rents, evictions, disrepair, and harassment.</p>
          </div>
          <a class="tel" href="tel:9173008159">917-300-8159</a>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://fifthave.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fifth Avenue Committee</a></h4>
            <p>South Brooklyn. Housing and tenant advocacy, affordable housing programs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://lossures.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Los Sures / Southside United HDFC</a></h4>
            <p>Southside Williamsburg. Organizes aggressively against displacement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://www.impacctbrooklyn.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IMPACCT Brooklyn</a></h4>
            <p>Central Brooklyn — Fort Greene, Clinton Hill, Bed-Stuy, Crown Heights, Prospect Heights.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://maketheroadny.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Make the Road New York</a></h4>
            <p>Bushwick. Tenant rights counseling and organizing, with an emphasis on Latin American and Caribbean immigrant communities. Also serves Queens and Staten Island.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="org">
          <div>
            <h4><a href="https://www.stnicksalliance.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">St. Nicks Alliance</a></h4>
            <p>Williamsburg and Greenpoint.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BRONX -->
