    <!-- ============ COALITIONS ============ -->
    <h2 style="margin-top:60px">Citywide &amp; statewide coalitions</h2>
    <p class="lead">These are the groups doing the political work — the ones who pass the laws that would have saved my building.</p>

    <div class="orgs">
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.uhab.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UHAB — Urban Homesteading Assistance Board</a> <span class="tagpill hot">Co-op conversion</span></h4>
          <p>Since 1973. They have taken roughly <strong>1,600 buildings</strong> from distressed rental into resident-owned affordable co-ops — over 1,300 HDFCs, 30,000+ homes, and a reported 99% success rate on conversions. They will come to your building and explain how it works. They also run <strong>HOPE (Housing Organizers for People Empowerment)</strong>, a member-led program training tenants in negotiation, legal rights, and collective action — it has built 20+ tenant associations in East Brooklyn alone. <strong>If you want your building to end up owned by the people in it, this is the call.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:2124793333">212-479-3333</a>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://housingjusticeforall.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Housing Justice for All</a> <span class="tagpill hot">TOPA</span></h4>
          <p>Statewide coalition of tenants and homeless New Yorkers. Leads the campaign for the Tenant Opportunity to Purchase Act. I served as volunteer co-chair of that campaign.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.neweconomyproject.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">New Economy Project</a> <span class="tagpill hot">COPA</span></h4>
          <p>Co-leads the fight for the Community Opportunity to Purchase Act, and runs organizing work to help tenants take their buildings into community ownership. If you want your building to end up tenant- or community-owned, start here.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://nyccli.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NYCCLI — NYC Community Land Initiative</a> <span class="tagpill hot">CLTs</span></h4>
          <p>Say it "nicely." An alliance of the city's community land trusts and housing justice groups — twenty CLT initiatives across all five boroughs. They'll come and run a workshop for your tenants association. Co-leads COPA, and with Housing Justice for All coordinates the statewide TOPA working group. <a href="mailto:info.nyccli@gmail.com">info.nyccli@gmail.com</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.neweconomyproject.org/cltmap/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Find your local community land trust</a></h4>
          <p>A map of every CLT in New York City. If your building is expiring, one of these could be the reason it stays affordable — permanently, not for another thirty years. <a href="/community-ownership/">How it works →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.righttocounselnyc.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Right to Counsel NYC Coalition</a></h4>
          <p>Won the country's first right to a lawyer in eviction cases. Now organizing to make it real.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.metcouncilonhousing.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Metropolitan Council on Housing</a></h4>
          <p>The city's oldest tenant organization. Hotline, walk-in clinic, and a deep library of tenant rights information.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.tandn.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tenants &amp; Neighbors</a></h4>
          <p>Statewide organizing and advocacy. Long history with expiring-subsidy buildings specifically.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:2126084320">212-608-4320</a>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://anhd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ANHD</a></h4>
          <p>Association for Neighborhood &amp; Housing Development. Research and policy — and the source of some of the sharpest data on this site.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ GOVERNMENT ============ -->
    <h2 style="margin-top:60px">Government offices</h2>
    <p class="lead">These offices exist to help you. Whether they do is a separate question — but use them, and put everything in writing.</p>

    <div class="orgs">
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/tenantprotection/index.page" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mayor's Office to Protect Tenants (MOPT)</a> <span class="tagpill hot">New</span></h4>
          <p>Revitalized on day one of the Mamdani administration and led by longtime tenant organizer Cea Weaver. It's the city's central body for defending tenants' rights and pushing agencies to act. It is brand new in this form — which means it is still deciding what it does. Tell them about LIHTC expiration.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/hpd/index.page" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HPD — Housing Preservation &amp; Development</a></h4>
          <p>The city housing agency. Holds regulatory agreements, runs preservation programs, and administers COPA if it becomes law.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="tel" href="tel:311">311</a>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://hcr.ny.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NYS Homes &amp; Community Renewal (HCR / DHCR)</a></h4>
          <p>The state agency. Administers LIHTC in New York, writes the Qualified Allocation Plan that sets our 30-year term, and holds your rent history. <strong>Request your building's regulatory agreement and rent history from them, in writing.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ TOOLS ============ -->
    <h2 style="margin-top:60px">Tools worth knowing</h2>

    <div class="orgs">
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://whoownswhat.justfix.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Who Owns What (JustFix)</a></h4>
          <p>Type in your address and see every other building your landlord owns, their violations, and their eviction filings. Free. If you're organizing, this is how you find the other tenants with the same landlord.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="https://preservationdatabase.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Housing Preservation Database</a></h4>
          <p>Every federally subsidized property in the country, with projected expiration dates. Free, but you have to register. It's what powers our registry.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="org">
        <div>
          <h4><a href="/find-your-building/">Our expiration registry</a></h4>
          <p>Search New York LIHTC buildings by address and see when the clock runs out.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="note" style="margin-top:48px">
      <b>This list is incomplete, and it will go out of date.</b>
      Organizations move, phone numbers change, groups fold and new ones start. If something here is
      wrong, or if your group belongs on it, <a href="/#join">tell me</a> and I'll fix it.
      <br><br>
      And to be clear: I'm not endorsing anyone or vouching for the quality of any particular
      organization's work. Some are excellent. Some are stretched thin. Call more than one.
    </div>

  </div>
</main>

<section class="section" style="background:var(--navy-d);color:#fff;text-align:center">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <h2 style="color:#fff">Don't call any of them alone.</h2>
    <p style="color:#a9bad3;margin-top:14px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.75">
      One tenant with a question is easy to ignore. A tenants association with a lawyer, an organizer,
      and a press list is a different building. Organize first — everything else gets easier.
    </p>
    <a href="/what-to-do/" class="btn btn-gold" style="margin-top:24px">Read the playbook</a>
  </div>
</section>
